author: @aat1f
text: How to make SQL Server 2022 Import and Export Data (64-bit) work? Here's what I did:  1-During installation of SQL Server 2022, make sure to install 'Database Engine Services' (this should be installed by default as this is core SQL feature) 'Integration Services' (important for importing tables into SQL)  2-I couldn't import the datasets using  Destination: 'SQL Server Native Client 11.0' in SQL Server 2022 Import and Export Data (64-bit). So I used Destination: 'Microsoft OLE DB Driver for SQL Server' aka MSOLEDBSQL and it worked.  2.1-Why? According to Microsoft's documentation, MSOLEDBSQL is new and recommended.

author: @ignacioespinola6407
text: If you #ERROR, You have to follow these steps (I don't know why but then it's like it activates itself):  1) In "Authentication"... instead of "Windows Authentication" choose the option "SQL Server Authentication" 2) It will ask you for the user "sa" and the password that you added in your installation. 3) Click the "Connect" button below 4) The "SQL Server Authentication" access will be activated for the first time 5) Now on the left side, where "SQL Server Authentication" opened (you'll notice why it wasn't there before), you have to right click on it and choose "Disconnect" 6) Then, go to the top left of the window, click on "File", click on "Connect Object Explorer". 7) The tab opens again from the start, where you will now choose "Windows Authentication" 8) Done, click "Connect" 9) YOU HAVE IT CONFIGURED AND READY TO USE! 10) God bless you all!

author: @ChaoticElegy
text: For those looking how to actually set up the server for the first time:  Hit the drop down for server name, hit the "browse" option, click the + sign next to database engine and select the computer name\SQLEXPRESS line and hit OK. Before hitting connect, select the options button and make sure "Trust server certificate" is checked off near the bottom. Hit connect and you will be connected.  If you do not see computer name\SQLEXPRESS make sure you installed the SQL Express download. Just select basic on it when it prompts.

author: @CortneyH83
text: Hi Everyone.  I was having trouble getting the SQL Express Server to connect to the Mangement Studio, but I found some answers below that helped.  Wanted to post them up top since @alextheanalyst has put together this great bootcamp for us all.    Thank you to @1Nyr6 who posted "To connect Studio to SQL server you need "computer name\SQLEXPRESS", to know the computer name, in search write: cmd, in opened admin panel write: hostname, and push Enter. Then put your hostname\SQLEXPRESS. Done."   And thank you to @euniceduah who posted "So I went to my PC, double click properties, you will find your device name ( that‚Äôs your computer name ). Now copy that name, then paste it here to ‚Äúcomputer name\SQLEXPRESS‚Äù , that simple"  If anyone can't find properties, I went to settings, system, about, copied my device name, went to management studio and pasted device name\SQLEXPRESS into the Server Name box.  Hope this helps : )
